         <a href="/" style="text-decoration: none;color: rgb(73, 73, 73);margin-right: 10px; margin-left: 10px; margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px; font-size: 1.5rem; font-weight: 600; text-transform: uppercase; font-family: 'Anek Gujarati', sans-serif;border-bottom: 1px solid rgb(73, 73, 73);padding-bottom: 0.5em;padding-top: 0.5em;">Home</a>
        <a href="/about" style="text-decoration: none;color: rgb(73, 73, 73); margin-right: 10px; margin-left: 10px; margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px; font-size: 1.5rem; font-weight: 600; text-transform: uppercase; font-family: 'Anek Gujarati', sans-serif;border-bottom: 1px solid rgb(73, 73, 73);padding-bottom: 0.5em;padding-top: 0.5em;">About</a>
        <a href="https://dharmpate.w3spaces.com/contact.html" style="text-decoration: none;color: rgb(73, 73, 73);margin-right: 10px;margin-left: 10px;margin-top: 10px;margin-bottom: 10px;font-size: 1.5rem;font-weight: 600;text-transform: uppercase;font-family: 'Anek Gujarati', sans-serif;border-bottom: 1px solid rgb(73, 73, 73);padding-bottom: 0.5em;padding-top: 0.5em;">Help</a>
    </header>
    <div>
        <main>
            <div class="faq-card">
                <ul class="faq-card__list">
                    <li class="faq-card__item">
                        <button class="faq-card__button faq-card__button_active">What is weather?<i
                                class="faq-card__icon fa fa-caret-down" aria-hidden="true"></i></button>
                        <p class="faq-card__desc">The day-to-day condition of the atmosphere at a place with respect to
                            the
                            temperature,â€‹ humidity, rainfall and wind speed, is called the weather.</p>
                    </li>
                    <li class="faq-card__item">
                        <button class="faq-card__button faq-card__button_active">how can i get weather?<i
                                class="faq-card__icon fa fa-caret-down" aria-hidden="true"></i></button>
                        <p class="faq-card__desc">In weather section search city and click on search button then you
                            will
                            get weather.</p>
                    </li>
                    <li class="faq-card__item">
                        <button class="faq-card__button faq-card__button_active">What is unit of temperature in this
                            web?<i class="faq-card__icon fa fa-caret-down" aria-hidden="true"></i></button>
                        <p class="faq-card__desc">temperature unit which is used in this web is fahrenhit degree.</p>
                    </li>
                    <li class="faq-card__item">
                        <button class="faq-card__button faq-card__button_active">What is uv index?<i
                                class="faq-card__icon fa fa-caret-down" aria-hidden="true"></i></button>
                        <p class="faq-card__desc">The UV Index is a measure of the level of UV radiation.</p>
                    </li>
                    <li class="faq-card__item">
                        <button class="faq-card__button faq-card__button_active">What is humidity?<i
                                class="faq-card__icon fa fa-caret-down" aria-hidden="true"></i></button>
                        <p class="faq-card__desc">Humidity is a measure of the amount of water vapor in the air.</p>
                    </li>
                    <li class="faq-card__item">
                        <button class="faq-card__button faq-card__button_active">What is cloudcover?<i
                                class="faq-card__icon fa fa-caret-down" aria-hidden="true"></i></button>
                        <p class="faq-card__desc">Cloud cover refers to the fraction of the sky obscured by clouds on
                            average when observed from a particular location.</p>
                    </li>
                    <li class="faq-card__item">
                        <button class="faq-card__button faq-card__button_active">What is mb in pressure?<i
